sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1896007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: We started from pBAD-GFPuv (GenBank: U62637.1, Clontech), applied the described mutations and codon optimised the sequence for ''E. coli''.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Variant of [[Part:BBa_K1896001|Part:BBa_K1896001]] where the start codon was replaced by a GSTGS linker so it can be used in C-terminal protein fusions.
mGFPuv2 contains the following mutations: * '''F99S/M153T/V163A''': GFPuv or ''cycle 3'' GFP was optimised for excitation by UV light (360-400nm). [1] * '''S208L''': Almost doubles the fluorescent intensity of GFPuv, resulting in GFPuv2. [2] * '''A206K''': Monomerizes most GFP variants by disrupting a hydrophobic patch. [3]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The start codon was replaced by a GSTGS linker to enable scarless C-terminal protein fusions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bob Van Hove, Maarten Van Brempt

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1896008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: INP<sub>RC</sub> is a truncated variant of the ''inaZ'' from ''Pseudomonas syringae'' ([[Part:BBa_K1896001|Part:BBa_K1896001]]), the N-terminal domain was removed in order to prevent localisation to the outer membrane, while still maintaining ice nucleation activity. No stop codon is present in this part to allow seamless assembly of fusion proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The repeat domain in this part seems to be impossible to create synthetically so PCR was used instead, with primers binding just outside of the repeat region. The absence of a stop codon allows for seamless assembly of fusion proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bob Van Hove, Maarten Van Brempt
